  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Occurs via direct blow or forceful contraction of quadriceps muscle\nDo not confuse a bipartite patella with a fracture (bipartite patellas are usually bilateral so may image contralateral knee to confirm)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Focal patellar tenderness, swelling, effusion\nCheck integrity of knee extensor mechanism by having patient perform straight-leg raise",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
